The locate Command:
-------------------

-> The fastest method to search for files in the Linux directory tree is to use the locate command.

    [root@server1 ~]# locate <filename>

-> The locate command looks in a premade database that contains a list of all the files on the system.

-> The database used for the locate command (/var/lib/mlocate/mlocate.db) is updated each day automatically and can be updated manually 
   by running the updatedb command at a command prompt.

-> You can configure the directories that are searched by the updatedb command by editing the /etc/updatedb.conf file.

*** A slower yet more versatile method for locating files on the filesystem is to use the find command.
